"""Built-in robot kinematics - one entry per FANUC robot type.

Each entry is a type's kinematic chain (axis home placements + faceplate -
the same published dimensions FANUC prints in its datasheet dimension
drawings), expressed as this app's own table; the viewer draws its own
schematic display from these numbers and no vendor file ships here.

Entries carrying a `validated` block have had forward kinematics through
their chain matched against real controllers' own position reports
(CURPOS TCP through the taught tool) - the block records how many robots
and how tightly. Entries without one are not yet checked against a
controller: a backup that carries its own position report still
self-verifies at runtime (a mismatch refuses to pose), but a backup
without one poses on the table's word alone, labeled unverified. See
modeldb.py for matching + per-robot flange measuring.
"""

